lead_paragraph: The college football spotlight article on Monday, about the evolution of Florida quarterback Tim Tebow, referred incompletely to the 100-meter dash time of Jeffrey Demps, a freshman running back who brings world-class speed to the Gators’ offense. Although he indeed was clocked in 10.25 seconds, he more recently ran the event in 10.01 seconds in June at the United States Olympic Trials.
